==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Draff
<hw>Draff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D. <ets>draf</ets>
the sediment of ale, Icel. <ets>draf</ets> draff, husks. Cf. 1st
<er>Drab</er>.]</ety> <def>Refuse; lees; dregs; the wash given to swine
or cows; hogwash; waste matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Prodigals lately come from swine keeping, from eating
<qex>draff</qex> and husks.</q> <rj><qau> Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>draff</qex> and offal of a bygone age.</q> <rj><qau>
Buckle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mere chaff and <qex>draff</qex>, much better burnt.</q> <rj><qau>
Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Draffish</ent>⟦br⟧
